# Response headers for the docs site (mirrors the hypermedia-components _headers).
#
# Headers apply in order; later rules layer on top of earlier ones. Astro's
# `_astro/` outputs are content-hashed, so they cache aggressively; HTML must stay
# revalidated so navigation keeps pace with the deployed build. Rules exist for both
# the bare and the /tesseraql-prefixed forms because the Worker strips the base path
# before the Static Assets binding matches.

/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: interest-cohort=()

/_astro/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/tesseraql/_astro/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/pagefind/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400

/tesseraql/pagefind/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400

/*.html
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
